Package us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D

Class Point3D32

  • java.lang.Object
    • us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.Point3D32
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Clearable, EpsilonComparable<Point3D32>, GeometricallyComparable<Point3D32>, GeometryObject<Point3D32>, Settable<Point3D32>, Transformable, Point3DBasics, Point3DReadOnly, Tuple3DBasics, Tuple3DReadOnly
    public class Point3D32
extends java.lang.Object
implements Point3DBasics, GeometryObject<Point3D32>
    A 3D point represents the 3D coordinates of a location in space.

    This version of 3D point uses single precision fields to save the value of each component. It is meant for garbage free usage and for situations where heap memory is limited. When memory is not a constraint, the use of Point3D is preferable.

    Author:
    Sylvain Bertrand

      • geometricallyEquals

        public boolean geometricallyEquals​(Point3D32 other,
                                   double epsilon)
        Tests if this and other represent the same point 3D to an epsilon.

        Two points are considered geometrically equal if they are at a distance of less than or equal to epsilon.

        Note that this.geometricallyEquals(other, epsilon) == true does not necessarily imply this.epsilonEquals(other, epsilon) and vice versa.

        Specified by:
        geometricallyEquals in interface GeometricallyComparable<Point3D32>
        Parameters:
        other - the other point 3D to compare against this. Not modified.
        epsilon - the maximum distance that the two points can be spaced and still considered equal.
        Returns:
        true if the two points represent the same geometry, false otherwise.
